   <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.0006"
      rolemaps-to="Part"
     >
    <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0007"
       xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
       Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
       rolemaps-to="P"
      >
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>The following examples are derived from 
     <Em xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0008"
       >
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>Homology manifold bordism
     </Em>
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> by Heather Johnston and Andrew Ranicki (Trans. Amer. Math. Soc. 352 no 11 (2000), PII: S 0002-9947(00)02630-1).
    </text>
   </text-unit>
   <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.0009"
      rolemaps-to="Part"
     >
    <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0010"
       xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
       Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
       rolemaps-to="P"
      >
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>
    </text>
   </text-unit>
   <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.0011"
      rolemaps-to="Part"
     >
    <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0012"
       xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
       Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
       rolemaps-to="P"
      >
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>The results of Johnston [5] on homology manifolds are extended here. It is not possible to investigate transversality by geometric methods—as in [5] we employ bordism and surgery instead.
    </text>
   </text-unit>
   <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.0013"
      rolemaps-to="Part"
     >
    <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0014"
       xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
       Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
       rolemaps-to="P"
      >
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>The proof of transversality is indirect, relying heavily on surgery theory—see Kirby and Siebenmann [7, III, §1], Marin [8] and Quinn [11]. We shall use the formulation in terms of topological block bundles of Rourke and Sanderson [12].
    </text>
   </text-unit>
   <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.0015"
      rolemaps-to="Part"
     >
    <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0016"
       xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
       Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
       rolemaps-to="P"
      >
     <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0017"
        title="math"
        af="mathml-1.xml tag-AFfile1.tex"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:Placement="Inline"
       >
       <AssociatedFile name="mathml-1.xml" xmlns="">
       <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"> <mi>𝑄</mi> </math>
       </AssociatedFile>
       <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile1.tex" xmlns="">
       $Q$
       </AssociatedFile>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>𝑄
     </Formula>
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> is a codimension 
     <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0018"
        title="math"
        af="mathml-2.xml tag-AFfile2.tex"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:Placement="Inline"
       >
       <AssociatedFile name="mathml-2.xml" xmlns="">
       <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"> <mi>𝑞</mi> </math>
       </AssociatedFile>
       <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile2.tex" xmlns="">
       $q$
       </AssociatedFile>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>𝑞
     </Formula>
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> subspace by Theorem 4.9 of Rourke and Sanderson [12]. (Hughes, Taylor and Williams [4] obtained a topological regular neighborhood theorem for arbitrary submanifolds ….)
    </text>
   </text-unit>
   <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.0019"
      rolemaps-to="Part"
     >
    <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0020"
       xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
       Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
       rolemaps-to="P"
      >
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>Wall [13, Chapter 11] obtained a codimension 
     <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0021"
        title="math"
        af="mathml-2.xml tag-AFfile3.tex"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:Placement="Inline"
       >
       <AssociatedFile name="mathml-2.xml" xmlns="">
       <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"> <mi>𝑞</mi> </math>
       </AssociatedFile>
       <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile3.tex" xmlns="">
       $q$
       </AssociatedFile>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>𝑞
     </Formula>
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> splitting obstruction ….
    </text>
   </text-unit>
   <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.0022"
      rolemaps-to="Part"
     >
    <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0023"
       xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
       Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
       rolemaps-to="P"
      >
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>… following the work of Cohen [2] on 
     <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0024"
        title="math"
        af="mathml-4.xml tag-AFfile4.tex"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:Placement="Inline"
       >
       <AssociatedFile name="mathml-4.xml" xmlns="">
       <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"> <mi>𝑃</mi> <mi>𝐿</mi> </math>
       </AssociatedFile>
       <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile4.tex" xmlns="">
       $PL$
       </AssociatedFile>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>𝑃𝐿
     </Formula>
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> manifold transversality.
    </text>
   </text-unit>
   <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.0025"
      rolemaps-to="Part"
     >
    <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0026"
       xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
       Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
       rolemaps-to="P"
      >
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>In this case each inverse image is automatically a 
     <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0027"
        title="math"
        af="mathml-4.xml tag-AFfile5.tex"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:Placement="Inline"
       >
       <AssociatedFile name="mathml-4.xml" xmlns="">
       <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"> <mi>𝑃</mi> <mi>𝐿</mi> </math>
       </AssociatedFile>
       <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile5.tex" xmlns="">
       $PL$
       </AssociatedFile>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>𝑃𝐿
     </Formula>
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> submanifold of codi
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>mension 
     <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0028"
        title="math"
        af="mathml-6.xml tag-AFfile6.tex"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:Placement="Inline"
       >
       <AssociatedFile name="mathml-6.xml" xmlns="">
       <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"> <mi>𝜎</mi> </math>
       </AssociatedFile>
       <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile6.tex" xmlns="">
       $\sigma $
       </AssociatedFile>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>𝜎
     </Formula>
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> (Cohen [2]), so there is no need to use 
     <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0029"
        title="math"
        af="mathml-7.xml tag-AFfile7.tex"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:Placement="Inline"
       >
       <AssociatedFile name="mathml-7.xml" xmlns="">
       <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"> <mi>𝑠</mi> </math>
       </AssociatedFile>
       <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile7.tex" xmlns="">
       $s$
       </AssociatedFile>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>𝑠
     </Formula>
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>-cobordisms.
    </text>
   </text-unit>
   <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.0030"
      rolemaps-to="Part"
     >
    <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0031"
       xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
       Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
       rolemaps-to="P"
      >
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>Quinn [10, 1.1] proved that …
    </text>
   </text-unit>
   <theorem-like xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.0032"
      rolemaps-to="Sect"
     >
    <Caption xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
       id="ID.0033"
      >
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>Theorem 
     <Lbl xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0034"
       >
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>3.1
     </Lbl>
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> (The additive structure of homology manifold bordism, Johnston [5])
    </Caption>
    <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0035"
       rolemaps-to="Part"
      >
     <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
        id="ID.0036"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
        rolemaps-to="P"
       >
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> …
     </text>
    </text-unit>
   </theorem-like>
   <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.0037"
      rolemaps-to="Part"
     >
    <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0038"
       xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
       Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
       rolemaps-to="P"
      >
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>For 
     <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0039"
        title="math"
        af="mathml-8.xml tag-AFfile8.tex"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:Placement="Inline"
       >
       <AssociatedFile name="mathml-8.xml" xmlns="">
       <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"> <mi>𝑚</mi> <mo lspace="0.278em" rspace="0.278em">≥</mo> <mn>5</mn> </math>
       </AssociatedFile>
       <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile8.tex" xmlns="">
       $m\geq 5$
       </AssociatedFile>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>𝑚≥5
     </Formula>
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> the Novikov-Wall surgery theory for topological manifolds gives an exact sequence (Wall [13, Chapter 10].
    </text>
   </text-unit>
   <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.0040"
      rolemaps-to="Part"
     >
    <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0041"
       xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
       Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
       rolemaps-to="P"
      >
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>The surgery theory of topological manifolds was extended to homology man
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>ifolds in Quinn [9, 10] and Bryant, Ferry, Mio and Weinberger [1].
    </text>
   </text-unit>
   <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.0042"
      rolemaps-to="Part"
     >
    <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0043"
       xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
       Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
       rolemaps-to="P"
      >
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>The 4-periodic obstruction is equivalent to an 
     <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0044"
        title="math"
        af="mathml-9.xml tag-AFfile9.tex"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:Placement="Inline"
       >
       <AssociatedFile name="mathml-9.xml" xmlns="">
       <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"> <mi>𝑚</mi> </math>
       </AssociatedFile>
       <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile9.tex" xmlns="">
       $m$
       </AssociatedFile>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>𝑚
     </Formula>
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>-dimensional homology man
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>ifold, by [1].
    </text>
   </text-unit>
   <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.0045"
      rolemaps-to="Part"
     >
    <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0046"
       xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
       Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
       rolemaps-to="P"
      >
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>Thus, the surgery exact sequence of [1] does not follow Wall [13] in relating homology manifold structures and normal invariants.
    </text>
   </text-unit>
   <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.0047"
      rolemaps-to="Part"
     >
    <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0048"
       xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
       Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
       rolemaps-to="P"
      >
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>… the canonical 
     <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0049"
        title="math"
        af="mathml-10.xml tag-AFfile10.tex"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:Placement="Inline"
       >
       <AssociatedFile name="mathml-10.xml" xmlns="">
       <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"> <mi>𝑇</mi> <mi>𝑂</mi> <mi>𝑃</mi> </math>
       </AssociatedFile>
       <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile10.tex" xmlns="">
       $TOP$
       </AssociatedFile>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>𝑇𝑂𝑃
     </Formula>
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> reduction ([3]) of the Spivak normal fibration of 
     <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0050"
        title="math"
        af="mathml-11.xml tag-AFfile11.tex"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:Placement="Inline"
       >
       <AssociatedFile name="mathml-11.xml" xmlns="">
       <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"> <mi>𝑀</mi> </math>
       </AssociatedFile>
       <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile11.tex" xmlns="">
       $M$
       </AssociatedFile>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>𝑀
     </Formula>
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> …
    </text>
   </text-unit>
   <theorem-like xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.0051"
      rolemaps-to="Sect"
     >
    <Caption xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
       id="ID.0052"
      >
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>Theorem 
     <Lbl xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0053"
       >
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>3.2
     </Lbl>
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> (Johnston [5])
    </Caption>
    <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0054"
       rolemaps-to="Part"
      >
     <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
        id="ID.0055"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
        rolemaps-to="P"
       >
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> …
     </text>
    </text-unit>
   </theorem-like>
   <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.0056"
      rolemaps-to="Part"
     >
    <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0057"
       xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
       Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
       rolemaps-to="P"
      >
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>Actually [5, (5.2)] is for 
     <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0058"
        title="math"
        af="mathml-12.xml tag-AFfile12.tex"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:Placement="Inline"
       >
       <AssociatedFile name="mathml-12.xml" xmlns="">
       <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"> <mi>𝑚</mi> <mo lspace="0.278em" rspace="0.278em">≥</mo> <mn>7</mn> </math>
       </AssociatedFile>
       <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile12.tex" xmlns="">
       $m\geq 7$
       </AssociatedFile>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>𝑚≥7
     </Formula>
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>, but we can improve to 
     <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0059"
        title="math"
        af="mathml-13.xml tag-AFfile13.tex"
        xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
        Layout:Placement="Inline"
       >
       <AssociatedFile name="mathml-13.xml" xmlns="">
       <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"> <mi>𝑚</mi> <mo lspace="0.278em" rspace="0.278em">≥</mo> <mn>6</mn> </math>
       </AssociatedFile>
       <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile13.tex" xmlns="">
       $m\geq 6$
       </AssociatedFile>
      <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>𝑚≥6
     </Formula>
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> by a slight variation of the proof as described below.
    </text>
   </text-unit>
   <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.0060"
      rolemaps-to="Part"
     >
    <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
       id="ID.0061"
       xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
       Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
       rolemaps-to="P"
      >
     <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>(This type of surgery on a Poincaré space is in the tradition of Lowell Jones [6].)
    </text>
   </text-unit>
